{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Eq2a4vou63znqTa6T8J931","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Sd4AngoRauazyeipHGviNm","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Verify story 20-3 runtime-provable","prompt":"Verify story 20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display using local runtime checks (runtime-provable tier).\n\nStory file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display.md\n\nThis story adds multi-lane event routing to the TUI renderer. It has 12 ACs — 10 are test-provable (verified via build/tests), 2 are runtime-provable (AC #4: Ctrl+L cycling, AC #12: performance at 15 FPS).\n\nExecute these steps and report results:\n\n1. Run the project build: `npm run build` in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness. Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n\n2. Run tests: `npm test` in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness. Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n\n3. Run linter if configured: check package.json for lint script. Report: PASS or FAIL + warning count.\n\n4. Run coverage: `npm run test:coverage` or check package.json for coverage script. Report: coverage percentage.\n\n5. For each of the 12 ACs in the story file, verify it. Read the story file first to understand all ACs:\n\n   **test-provable ACs (1,2,3,5,6,7,8,9,10,11)** — verify via:\n   - Check test files exist: `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer-lanes.test.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane-activity-header.test.tsx`\n   - Grep for specific test names matching each AC\n   - Check function/method existence via grep (e.g., processLaneEvent, updateMergeState, laneId parameter on update())\n   - Check test output for relevant test results\n   \n   **runtime-provable ACs (4, 12):**\n   - AC #4 (Ctrl+L cycling): Since this is a TUI app that requires interactive terminal, check:\n     - useInput hook exists in ink-app.tsx for Ctrl+L\n     - Test exists for Ctrl+L cycling behavior  \n     - The cycling logic exists in ink-renderer.tsx\n     - Run any existing test for this behavior\n   - AC #12 (Performance 15 FPS, <5ms overhead): Check:\n     - Performance test exists in test files\n     - Run the performance test and check results\n     - The event routing code path is efficient (no unnecessary re-renders)\n\n   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n\n6. Generate proof document at /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display-proof.md with evidence from each check. \n\nIMPORTANT: The proof document MUST follow this exact format for each AC:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Proof: 20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display\n\n## AC 1: [description from story]\n\n**Tier:** test-provable\n**Verdict:** PASS (or FAIL)\n\nEvidence:\n\n```bash\n[command that was run]\n```\n\n```output\n[actual output from the command]\n```\n\n[Repeat ## AC N sections for all 12 ACs]\n```\n\nUse `## AC N:` headers (level 2, not level 3). Use `**Verdict:**` not `**Result:**`. Use `**Tier:**` with double asterisks. Include ```bash and ```output code blocks for evidence.\n\n7. Run `npx codeharness verify --story 20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display` to validate the proof format.\n\n8. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, missing files, unexpected behavior)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky or suboptimal)\n- Verification gaps (ACs that were hard to verify, weak evidence)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n-