{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016aqfvex84DbGXXifeTKpyR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 20.3: Lane Event Routing & Activity Display\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want the activity section to show the most recently active lane's tool calls,\n11\tso that I can see what's happening without noise from all lanes.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** multiple lanes producing stream events concurrently, **when** a `StreamEvent` arrives from a lane, **then** `ink-renderer.tsx` routes the event to the correct per-lane state (tools, thoughts, retries) based on a `laneId` parameter on the `update()` method. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** the renderer is receiving events from multiple lanes, **when** the activity section renders, **then** it shows events (completed tools, active tool, last thought, retry notice) from the most recently active lane only — not a merged stream from all lanes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** the activity section is showing lane 1's events, **when** lane 2 produces a new stream event, **then** the activity section automatically switches to show lane 2's events (most-recently-active heuristic). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** a multi-lane TUI, **when** `Ctrl+L` is pressed, **then** the displayed lane in the activity section cycles to the next active lane (wrapping around), overriding the most-recently-active heuristic until a new event arrives from a different lane. <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** the activity section is showing a specific lane's events, **when** rendered, **then** a lane indicator `[Lane {N} ▸]` is displayed in the activity header showing which lane's activity is currently visible. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** `max_parallel: 1` (single lane mode), **when** the TUI renders, **then** no lane indicator is displayed and the activity section behaves identically to the current single-lane TUI — no event routing logic engaged. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** a lane event of type `lane-started`, **when** the renderer processes it, **then** the lane is added to the renderer's lane state map and becomes available for activity display and routing. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** a lane event of type `lane-completed`, **when** the renderer processes it, **then** the lane's final state is preserved for display but the lane is removed from the active rotation for `Ctrl+L` cycling. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** a lane event of type `lane-failed`, **when** the renderer processes it, **then** the lane is marked as failed in the TUI (lane status shows error state), the activity section does not freeze, and the TUI continues rendering other active lanes (NFR6 — crash isolation). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** a `LaneEvent` with type `lane-completed` and an `EngineResult`, **when** processed by the renderer, **then** the summary bar's `doneStories` and `pendingEpics` lists are updated to reflect the completed epic. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t11. **Given** merge events (from the merge serialization pipeline), **when** the renderer processes them, **then** the `mergeState` field on `RendererState` is updated and `MergeStatus` re-renders with the current merge progress (clean, resolved, escalated, in-progress). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t12. **Given** the TUI is rendering at `maxFps: 15` with 4 concurrent lanes each producing stream events, **when** measured, **then** the render loop does not drop below 15 FPS and event routing adds less than 5ms overhead per event (NFR2). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n40\t\n41\t- [x] Task 1: Extend `RendererHandle` and `RendererState` for multi-lane event routing (AC: #1, #6, #7, #8, #9)\n42\t  - [x] Add `laneId?: string` parameter to `RendererHandle.update()` signature\n43\t  - [x] Add `activeLaneId: string | null` field to `RendererState` (tracks which lane's activity is displayed)\n44\t  - [x] Add `laneStates: Map<string, LaneActivityState>` to renderer controller (per-lane tools, thoughts, retries)\n45\t  - [x] Define `LaneActivityState` interface: `{ completedTools: CompletedToolEntry[], activeTool: { name: string } | null, activeToolArgs: string, lastThought: string | null, retryInfo: RetryInfo | null, activeDriverName: string | null, status: 'active' | 'completed' | 'failed' }`\n46\t  - [x] Route `update()` events to per-lane state when `laneId` is provided\n47\t  - [x] Copy active lane's state to top-level `RendererState` fields for display\n48\t  - [x] When `laneId` is undefined (single-lane mode), behave exactly as today — no routing\n49\t\n50\t- [x] Task 2: Add `processLaneEvent()` method to `RendererHandle` (AC: #7, #8, #9, #10)\n51\t  - [x] Define method: `processLaneEvent(event: LaneEvent): void`\n52\t  - [x] Handle `lane-started`: create entry in `laneStates` map, update `activeLaneId` if first lane\n53\t  - [x] Handle `lane-completed`: mark lane as completed, update `summaryBar` props (move epic stories to `doneStories`, remove from `pendingEpics`)\n54\t  - [x] Handle `lane-failed`: mark lane as failed, do NOT remove from display, do NOT freeze TUI\n55\t  - [x] Handle `epic-queued`: update `summaryBar.pendingEpics` list\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 3: Add `updateMergeState()` method to `RendererHandle` (AC: #11)\n58\t  - [x] Define method: `updateMergeState(mergeState: MergeState | null): void`\n59\t  - [x] Set `state.mergeState` and trigger rerender\n60\t  - [x] Also update `summaryBar.mergingEpic` to reflect current merge status\n61\t\n62\t- [x] Task 4: Implement most-recently-active lane tracking (AC: #2, #3)\n63\t  - [x] On each `update()` call with a `laneId`, record `lastActivityTime` for that lane\n64\t  - [x] When `laneId` differs from current `activeLaneId`, switch displayed lane unless user has pinned via `Ctrl+L`\n65\t  - [x] Copy the new active lane's state to the top-level display fields\n66\t\n67\t- [x] Task 5: Implement `Ctrl+L` cycling (AC: #4)\n68\t  - [x] Add `useInput` hook in `ink-app.tsx` to listen for `Ctrl+L`\n69\t  - [x] On `Ctrl+L`, cycle `activeLaneId` to next active lane (skip completed/failed lanes)\n70\t  - [x] Set a `pinnedLane` flag that suppresses auto-switch until a new lane event arrives from a different lane\n71\t  - [x] Wrap around from last lane to first\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 6: Add lane indicator to activity section (AC: #5, #6)\n74\t  - [x] Create `LaneActivityHeader` component showing `[Lane {N} ▸]` prefix\n75\t  - [x] Render above `CompletedTools` when `laneCount > 1`\n76\t  - [x] Do not render when `laneCount <= 1` (backward compat)\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 7: Wire lane events from `lane-pool.ts` through `run.ts` to renderer (AC: #7, #8, #9)\n79\t  - [x] In `run.ts` (or parallel execution orchestrator), subscribe to `LaneEvent` emissions from the lane pool\n80\t  - [x] Call `renderer.processLaneEvent(event)` for each `LaneEvent`\n81\t  - [x] Pass `laneId` (epic ID) to `renderer.update(event, driverName, laneId)` for stream events\n82\t\n83\t- [x] Task 8: Wire merge events to renderer (AC: #11)\n84\t  - [x] In the merge execution pipeline (where `worktree-manager.merge()` and `merge-agent` are called), emit `MergeState` updates\n85\t  - [x] Call `renderer.updateMergeState(mergeState)` at each stage: in-progress, clean, resolved, escalated\n86\t\n87\t- [x] Task 9: Write unit tests for event routing in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #6, #7, #8, #9, #10, #11)\n88\t  - [x] Test: events with laneId are routed to per-lane state\n89\t  - [x] Test: activity section shows most recently active lane's events\n90\t  - [x] Test: auto-switch to new lane when event arrives from different lane\n91\t  - [x] Test: single-lane mode (no laneId) behaves identically to pre-20-3\n92\t  - [x] Test: processLaneEvent lane-started creates lane state\n93\t  - [x] Test: processLaneEvent lane-completed marks lane done, updates summaryBar\n94\t  - [x] Test: processLaneEvent lane-failed marks lane failed, does not freeze\n95\t  - [x] Test: updateMergeState updates mergeState on RendererState\n96\t  - [x] Test: no lane indicator rendered when laneCount <= 1\n97\t\n98\t- [x] Task 10: Write integration tests for `ink-app.tsx` with lane indicator (AC: #5)\n99\t  - [x] Test: `[Lane N ▸]` indicator renders in activity section when laneCount > 1\n100\t  - [x] Test: lane indicator not rendered when laneCount <= 1\n101\t\n102\t- [x] Task 11: Performance validation (AC: #12)\n103\t  - [x] Test: routing 4 lanes of events does not cause measurable render delay\n104\t  - [x] Test: event routing overhead is within acceptable bounds (< 5ms per event)\n105\t\n106\t## Dev Notes\n107\t\n108\t### Architecture Constraints\n109\t\n110\t- **Architecture Decision 8** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The renderer receives events from all active lanes and routes them by lane ID. Only the most recently active lane shows in the activity section.\n111\t- **Single Ink instance**: All components feed into the same Ink render loop. Event routing happens in the controller (ink-renderer.tsx), not in components.\n112\t- **NFR2**: Multi-lane TUI must render at 15 FPS with up to 4 concurrent lanes. Event routing must not introduce perceptible overhead.\n113\t- **NFR6**: Crash in one lane must not freeze the TUI. A failed lane's event stream ends; the renderer marks it as failed and continues rendering other lanes.\n114\t- **NFR10**: `maxParallel: 1` must produce behavior identical to current single-lane TUI.\n115\t\n116\t### What This Story Actually Does\n117\t\n118\tThis story wires live data into the multi-lane TUI components created in 20-1 and 20-2:\n119\t\n120\t1. **Event routing** — StreamEvents are tagged with `laneId` and routed to per-lane state in the renderer.\n121\t2. **Activity display filtering** — The activity section (CompletedTools, ActiveTool, LastThought, RetryNotice) shows only the most recently active lane's events.\n122\t3. **Lane lifecycle** — LaneEvents (started, completed, failed) are processed to manage lane state and update the summary bar.\n123\t4. **Merge status wiring** — MergeState updates flow from the merge pipeline to the renderer.\n124\t5. **Ctrl+L cycling** — User can manually cycle which lane's activity is displayed.\n125\t6. **Lane indicator** — `[Lane N ▸]` shows which lane is currently displayed in the activity section.\n126\t\n127\t### Key Files to Modify\n128\t\n129\t| File | Why |\n130\t|------|-----|\n131\t| `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` | Add per-lane state, event routing, processLaneEvent, updateMergeState |\n132\t| `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` | Add `useInput` for Ctrl+L, render lane indicator |\n133\t| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | Extend `RendererState` with `activeLaneId` |\n134\t| `src/commands/run.ts` | Wire lane events and stream events with laneId to renderer |\n135\t\n136\t### Key Files to Create\n137\t\n138\t| File | Why |\n139\t|------|-----|\n140\t| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer-lanes.test.ts` | Unit tests for multi-lane event routing |\n141\t\n142\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n143\t\n144\t| File | Why |\n145\t|------|-----|\n146\t| `src/lib/ink-summary-bar.tsx` | `SummaryBar`, `SummaryBarProps` — receives data from routing |\n147\t| `src/lib/ink-merge-status.tsx` | `MergeStatus`, `MergeState` — receives data from routing |\n148\t| `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` | `LaneContainer`, `LaneData` — lane layout |\n149\t| `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` | `Lane`, `StoryProgressEntry` — per-lane display |\n150\t| `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` | `CompletedTools`, `ActiveTool`, `LastThought`, `RetryNotice` — activity section |\n151\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LaneEvent`, `LaneStatus`, `EpicResult` — lane lifecycle events |\n152\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | `MergeResult` — merge outcome types |\n153\t| `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` | `MergeConflictContext` — conflict resolution types |\n154\t| `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` | `StreamEvent` — event types that get routed per lane |\n155\t\n156\t### Component Hierarchy (Target State After 20-3)\n157\t\n158\t```\n159\t<App>\n160\t  <Header />                       ← Extended (20-1) with lane count\n161\t  <LaneContainer>                  ← Created (20-1)\n162\t    <Lane epic={10}> ... </Lane>\n163\t    <Lane epic={14}> ... </Lane>\n164\t    <CollapsedLanes />\n165\t  </LaneContainer>\n166\t  <Separator />\n167\t  <SummaryBar />                   ← Created (20-2), wired by 20-3\n168\t  <Separator />\n169\t  <MergeStatus />                  ← Created (20-2), wired by 20-3\n170\t  <Separator />\n171\t  <LaneActivityHeader />           ← NEW (20-3): [Lane N ▸]\n172\t  <CompletedTools />               ← Existing: now lane-filtered\n173\t  <ActiveTool />                   ← Existing: now lane-filtered\n174\t  <LastThought />                  ← Existing: now lane-filtered\n175\t  <RetryNotice />                  ← Existing: now lane-filtered\n176\t</App>\n177\t```\n178\t\n179\t### Event Flow Architecture\n180\t\n181\t```\n182\tlane-pool.ts                    stream-parser.ts\n183\t  │ LaneEvent                     │ StreamEvent + laneId\n184\t  │                               │\n185\t  ▼                               ▼\n186\trun.ts ─── renderer.processLaneEvent(e) ───► per-lane state map\n187\t       ─── renderer.update(e, driver, laneId) ──► per-lane activity state\n188\t       ─── renderer.updateMergeState(ms) ──────► RendererState.mergeState\n189\t                                                   │\n190\t                                                   ▼\n191\t                                          activeLaneId selects\n192\t                                          which lane's activity\n193\t                                          to copy to top-level\n194\t                                          RendererState fields\n195\t                                                   │\n196\t                                                   ▼\n197\t                                            <App> re-renders\n198\t```\n199\t\n200\t### Existing Patterns to Follow\n201\t\n202\t- **Component file naming**: `ink-{name}.tsx` — pure presentational components.\n203\t- **Import style**: `import React from 'react'` + `import { Text, Box } from 'ink'` — standard Ink pattern.\n204\t- **ESM imports**: Use `.js` extensions in TypeScript ESM imports.\n205\t- **useInput hook**: Ink provides `useInput(handler)` for keyboard input handling.\n206\t- **Symbols**: Done `✓`, active `◆`, pending `○`, spinner `◌`, lane indicator `▸`.\n207\t- **Color scheme**: Green for success/done, yellow for warnings/in-progress, red for failure, dim for inactive/pending.\n208\t- **Status prefixes**: `[OK]`, `[FAIL]`, `[WARN]`, `[INFO]` — established pattern.\n209\t- **Ink testing**: Use `ink-testing-library` render function. See `src/lib/__tests__/ink-*.test.tsx`.\n210\t- **Renderer testing**: Call `startRenderer()` with `_forceTTY: true`, call methods, check `_getState()`.\n211\t\n212\t### Edge Cases\n213\t\n214\t- **No laneId on update()**: Single-lane mode — route to top-level state directly (backward compat).\n215\t- **All lanes completed/failed**: Activity section shows last active lane's final state. `Ctrl+L` has no lanes to cycle to.\n216\t- **Lane event for unknown laneId**: Create new lane state on-the-fly (defensive).\n217\t- **Ctrl+L with only 1 active lane**: No-op (nothing to cycle to).\n218\t- **Rapid lane switching**: Auto-switch heuristic should not cause flicker — only switch on first event from a new lane, not on every event.\n219\t- **Merge events during single-lane**: Should still update `mergeState` but `MergeStatus` won't render (guarded by `laneCount > 1` in ink-app.tsx).\n220\t- **Lane pool emits events after renderer cleanup**: `processLaneEvent` should check `cleaned` flag.\n221\t\n222\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n223\t\n224\t- **LaneContainer creation** — Already done in 20-1.\n225\t- **SummaryBar / MergeStatus components** — Already done in 20-2.\n226\t- **Ctrl+M merge detail toggle** — Out of scope for MVP; could be a follow-up story.\n227\t- **Merge execution logic** — Already exists in `worktree-manager.ts` (18-1) and `merge-agent.ts` (18-2).\n228\t- **Lane pool scheduling** — Already exists in `lane-pool.ts` (17-2).\n229\t- **Epic flow execution** — Already exists from 19-2.\n230\t\n231\t### Previous Stories Intelligence\n232\t\n233\t- Story 20-1 created `ink-lane.tsx` and `ink-lane-container.tsx`. Extended `Header` with `laneCount` and `laneTotalCost`. Added `lanes?: LaneData[]` to `RendererState`.\n234\t- Story 20-2 created `ink-summary-bar.tsx` and `ink-merge-status.tsx`. Added `summaryBar` and `mergeState` to `RendererState`. Integrated into `ink-app.tsx` conditional on `laneCount > 1`.\n235\t- `ink-renderer.tsx` currently has no multi-lane awareness — it manages a single flat state. This story adds the routing layer.\n236\t- `RendererHandle.update()` currently takes `(event, driverName?)`. This story adds an optional `laneId` third parameter.\n237\t- Testing pattern: vitest, `vi.mock`, `ink-testing-library`, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`.\n238\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`.\n239\t\n240\t### Project Structure Notes\n241\t\n242\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n243\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n244\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n245\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n246\t- Keep files under 300 lines (NFR from architecture)\n247\t\n248\t### References\n249\t\n250\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 20.3]\n251\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 8 -- Multi-Lane TUI Architecture]\n252\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Ctrl+L -- Cycle Active Lane Display]\n253\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Component Architecture]\n254\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx]\n255\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx]\n256\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx#RendererState]\n257\t- [Source: src/lib/lane-pool.ts#LaneEvent]\n258\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx]\n259\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sd4AngoRauazyeipHGviNm","session_id":"8d435a21-6a50-4823-af76-9ebae9daeba7","uuid":"172d5d62-e6c0-4791-96ba-62268c2e16ee","timestamp":"2026-04-04T03:25:36.716Z"}
