{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SwZbipFGhK76v2cWicLKLX","type":"tool_result","content":"0\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-04\n1\t\n2\t**Generated:** 2026-04-04T00:15:00Z\n3\t\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\t## 1. Session Summary\n7\t\n8\t### Stories Attempted This Session\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phase Reached | Outcome |\n11\t|-------|--------------|---------|\n12\t| 17-1-worktree-manager | done (committed) | Completed prior session, committed as `c5385bf` |\n13\t| 17-2-lane-pool | verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed; currently in verification |\n14\t\n15\t### Sprint Progress (Cumulative)\n16\t\n17\t- **Total stories:** 64\n18\t- **Done:** 48 (75%)\n19\t- **In progress (verifying):** 1 (17-2-lane-pool)\n20\t- **Backlog:** 15 (epics 17-20 remainder)\n21\t- **Failed:** 0\n22\t- **Epics completed:** 16 of 20\n23\t\n24\t### Session Velocity\n25\t\n26\tThis session processed 2 stories through the pipeline. Story 17-1 was committed from a prior session's work. Story 17-2 completed all three subagent phases (create-story, dev-story, code-review) and is awaiting verification.\n27\t\n28\t---\n29\t\n30\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n31\t\n32\t### Issues from Session Log\n33\t\n34\t**Category: State Regression (1 issue)**\n35\t- Sprint-status.yaml showed 17-1-worktree-manager regressed from `done` to `backlog` despite being committed. Required manual fix.\n36\t- **Root cause:** sprint-status.yaml is a derived view regenerated from sprint-state.json. If the generator runs before sprint-state.json is updated, it overwrites correct status.\n37\t- **Severity:** Medium. Causes confusion but doesn't block execution.\n38\t\n39\t**Category: Design Decisions (2 issues)**\n40\t- AC #5 epic independence ordering uses simplified heuristic (batch parallelism, not sliding-window). Epic 3 won't start until ALL of epics 1+2 finish, even if epic 1 finishes early. Correct per spec but limits throughput.\n41\t- `createWorktree` uses `execSync`, blocking the event loop. Inherited from WorktreeManager design — acceptable for MVP but needs async refactor for production parallel execution.\n42\t\n43\t**Category: Code Quality (2 issues)**\n44\t- Unreachable defensive code: `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard flagged as LOW by code review. Left in place as harmless.\n45\t- No test for pool reuse (calling `startPool` twice). Minor gap — not a regression risk.\n46\t\n47\t**Category: Coverage (1 issue)**\n48\t- 3 MEDIUM coverage gaps found during code review — all fixed. Final coverage: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines.\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0134YJKBXbjt3SerRqP8fQa3","session_id":"8d435a21-6a50-4823-af76-9ebae9daeba7","uuid":"1243d005-0452-4e1e-b99f-f3b01fcdda28","timestamp":"2026-04-04T03:32:16.069Z"}
