tifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nThis session completed 1 story:\n- 20-3-lane-event-routing-activity-display: verifying → done (Tier C, runtime-provable verification, ALL_PASS 12/12)\n- Epic 20 marked done (all 3 stories complete)\n\nThis was a quick session — the story was already at `verifying` status with all code complete from a previous session. Only verification was needed.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-04.md.\n\nSince a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"adb1401b09089e62b","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-04.md`.\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\n- **Session 9** was a verification-only session. Story 20-3 passed ALL_PASS 12/12, completing Epic 20 and the entire sprint (95 stories, 20 epics).\n- **Biggest cost problem:** Verification phase consumes 45.3% ($183.71) of total sprint cost ($405.61), driven by subagents running the same tests 3-4x redundantly.\n- **Code review earned its keep:** 9.5% of cost, caught 3 HIGH security bugs (shell injection) across the sprint.\n- **14 LOW tech debt items** accumulated unfixed across sessions — needs a cleanup backlog.\n- **Top action:** Cap verification test runs to 2 max and capture output for reparse instead of re-running."}],"totalDurationMs":98188,"totalTokens":34614,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2904,"cache_read_input_tokens":31475,"output_tokens":234,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2904},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
